Dan, as per my voice-mail, I talked to Hunter and he confirmed that Enron
would notify BP/Crestar via e-mail by 9:45 MST of the contracts with
associated volumes. On the chance that Enron cannot notify BP/Crestar or
fails to take, and BP/Crestar incur penalty costs then Enron would pay for
those as per point number #2 below ie.,

[ (2) Add a clause to either the Enron agreement or the Gulf assignment
agreement to state if Enron fails to inform and/or take, then any penalty
costs/price difference incurred by Crestar/BP shall be passed onto Enron.]

Hunter agreed as long as there is a reciprocal clause that Enron is
compensated when BP/Crestar fail to nominate by the 10:30am MST Timely
cycle deadline and Enron incurs costs, then BP/Crestar would pay those
costs.

Crestar and BP both agree with the reciprocal cost provisions. Now it is a
matter of where the language should go. I think it should be in the Enron
contract.

Please advise if you agree and how we should proceed to include the
language in the Enron contract.

